dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  pm-atfm,related,"2026-07-11T16:22:48.239Z",null,null
body: "Promoted from the pm-mpbb DX ledger (candidate lever a) on 2026-07-11, when the pm-a22j baseline gate opened (full AC met: checked-in script scripts/measure-agent-token-surface.mjs + MCP tools/list = 32,979 B ~= 8.2k tok / 28 tools).\n\nThe a22j baseline measures the cost of the SURFACE (help/contracts/tools-list payload sizes). Nothing measures what an agent actually pays per completed task: tokens read + retries burned across a realistic command sequence. Without that, DX regressions (verbose new output, envelope bloat, extra confirmation rounds) stay invisible until a human notices.\n\nApproach (per the ledger fence: extend, never a new harness):\n- Record golden agent transcripts (ordered pm command sequences with expected envelopes) for a handful of canonical tasks: triage-and-claim, create-with-deps, close-with-resolution, context bootstrap.\n- Replay them against the current build and report total bytes/approx-tokens per completed task.\n- Wire the result into the existing token-cost CI gate lineage (pm-cu1i, shipped PR#487) with a documented regression threshold, exactly like the changelog and contracts drift gates.\n\nBoundary: pm-atfm (related) grades context/next assembly QUALITY with rank-aware metrics; this item measures token COST per task. Keep the corpora separate; the replay runner may share golden-workspace fixtures."
